Options: <event>[+lo][-hi]  dt=<time>  idt=<time>  collect[=tm]\
         toobrief=<time>  toosmall=<dist (pixels)>  postfix=<string>\
  Measures reversals within dt of an event.\
  Default event is ::all, which measures all reversals.\
  Any output type save custom can be used as a trigger event (speed, tap, etc.)\
    Adding +lo triggers when output goes above lo (default is lo==0)\
    Adding -hi triggers when output goes below hi (default is hi==infinity)\
    For example, ::speed+0.2 looks for reversals after animal reaches 0.2mm/s\
    Stimuli like ::tap work without needing to specify limits.\
  Reversals starting within dt after the event are counted (default=1s)\
    If a reversal ends and another begins within dt, it is appended to the next\
    A reversal already in progress before the event is ignored.\
  Alternatively, any pair of events with less than time idt between them\
    are merged into a single event (default = 0)\
  Reversals that take too little time or space can be excluded\
    using toobrief and toosmall (defaults = 0)\
  ::collect places everything in one file; default is one file per object.\
    =tm gives a histogram of the results, grouped in windows tm wide (tm>0)\
    If trigger events are used, the histogram bins by trigger time\
